    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/35.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Your number 30, September 21. War Office requests date and place of birth and
                    parent’s name John Ciappone. Give similar information concerning all other
                    cases.</p>
                <p>Government finds it most difficult to reply officially permitting subjects,
                    naturalization America, to escape military service without granting similar
                    privileges to certain other countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
